    {
      "content": "Reactive column grids consist of columns, gutter, and margins to provide a convenient structure for the layout of elements within the body area. Components align with column grids to ensur ze a consistent layout across screen sizes and directions.\nAs the content area grows or decreases in size, the number of grid columns changes accordingly.",
      "source": {
        "artboard": "Pattern_Dashboard responsive",
        "layerName": "Text Copy 2",
        "objectID": "BF75B051-DE91-41BC-B8D1-AA1E055A48F3"
      }
    },
    {
      "content": "When the user resizes the window, the width of the card increases until the next break point. After the break point, the number of columns increases.",
